data.title: Great Place!
data.text:
Located in a nicely renovated space in Bellinghams downtown. The is small and clean. 
The food came quick and hot. My wife had the Chicken Mole and it was super good. I has Carne Asala and it was good too.
Can't say enough about the friendly staff too.
Always nice to patronize a professionally run mom and pop restaurant that exceeds our expectations.
Reasonably price too!

data.title: Homemade Goodness! Warm Hospitality
data.text:
After spending a couple days around the area, we opted for a less busy spot for dinner downtown Bellingham. The owner was a kind older gent with gracious manners and the warmest hospitality. This was just the beginning of our evening.
I sampled a local beer: Aslan, which was cold and only $4 for a pint.
The bottomless chips and salsa were complementary--the salsa homemade and a medium spiciness.
We opted for the fajitas for two ($23): a large stack of homemade corn tortillas (you can choose flour) and (we chose) steak. The cook in the open kitchen over yonder cooked our meal to order with fresh bell peppers, onions and an oily sauce that was tinged dark orange, but I could not decipher. It was undoubtedly their homemade recipe. We eat got a large dinner place teeming with refried beans and rice and a small bit of shredded lettuce.
I'm not a huge fajita eater, so I cannot compare to many others. I do know that we had enough leftovers for both of us for lunch the next day. Although the tortillas did not keep very well, so we ate the leftovers in a bun.
Great value. Very clean! I'd definitely go back again.

data.title: Amazing!
data.text: Six of us stopped in on the way back to Canada and everything we ate was awesome. I can't recommend this place enough. Food was awesome, the drinks were awesome and the staff were so nice. You'd be nuts not to stop here if you want a great feed and time.

data.title: REAL MEXICAN!
data.text: So very pleased with the menu ... from the Shrimp Cocktail to the "Dessert" offerings.  The food quality & prep was close to perfection as well as being served @ proper temp.  True Mexican fare with proper choice in "spiciness".  Will most definitely return to this location.

data.title: Great food
data.text: Small but quaint family run restaurant. It reminded me of being in Mexico. The food is excellant with very hospitable service. The staff and owner made you feel like you were in their home not an eatery.

data.title: Yummmmmm!
data.text: Stopped in based off a recommendation and we weren't disappointed.  Tastes much more authentic than the typical Mexican restaurants around.  Small venue but regardless, food is yummy and fresh.  We had the soft shell tacos, nachos and a gigantic margarita that may or may not have been missing the mixer 😀. All in all a great dinner and we'll be back for sure.

data.title: Felt like being in Mexico, right there in Bellingham!
data.text: A small and colorful spot in downtown Bellingham with very friendly wait staff. The food is authentic and portions are very, very generous. Loved the shrimp burrito with large shrimp inside! Excellent chips and salsa to start.

data.title: Very good small family owned Mexican eatery
data.text: This place is a small place on a major street.  It gets lots of customers.  It isn't fancy but the food is very good.  Price is good and they have specials to take out, i.e. a dozen tamales.

data.title: Muy autentico
data.text: Had a quick dinner here and it was great. Taco plate, fried jalapenos, and an ice cold tecate. Proprietor was very gracious. I noticed a young couple next to me sharing the ginormous margarita. I will certainly visit again.

data.title: Great lunch spot!
data.text: I really like this place - good sopas and enchiladas and really friendly owners. The prices are fantastic too and it's never too crowded.

data.title: Just loved it
data.text: We were walking about after the farmers market and noticed the sign saying, best tamales. Dubious as we have seen signs like this before. We were warmly greeted and ordered 2 Mojitos. These babies had a kick, and if I was not driving we would have ordered a couple more. The tamales were so good we took a dozen to go. Do not walk here, run. Gracias

data.title: Be sure to order a tamale
data.text:
This was our first time at Tadeo's.   The menu is fairly traditional Mexican with some obvious house specialties, and it looks like breakfast might be the meal to go back for next time.   Lots of unusual choices on the early menu, and not that many Mex joints are open early in the day.    

To share, we ordered a two-tamale combo plate, one chicken/red sauce and one pork/green sauce, both of which were very, very good.   Home-made tamales aren't easy to come by in this town and these were generously portioned.    Came with rice and beans, and everything was tasteful and well-seasoned.   We also ordered two carne asada tacos a la carte, which were served on fresh, made-in-house tortillas.   These rocked.   Chips and a very good house salsa were complimentary.  

Must mention the outstanding service:   we were waited on by a very elegant, polite older gentleman who I sensed might be the owner.   When he took our order, he deduced that we were going to share so he brought two warm plates so that we could create individual portions from the platters.   Not everybody in restaurants thinks that way, let alone does it voluntarily.   He also brought an ice cold glass for the beer, also unasked.   This is a small family business, and it shows in such attentive service.   

We also liked the Mexican music.   We can't understand a word of it, but it adds great atmosphere!   

We'll be back.

data.title: Fresh, flavorful, and authentic
data.text: We enjoyed lunch here and flavors are vibrant, fresh, and real Mexican.  The family takes great pride and it shows in every dish served. The mole has a deep, rich flavor that will make you feel like you're back in Mexico.  The price is right and frankly very inexpensive for the quality and portions they deliver.  If you're in Bellingham, please try this place.

data.title: Homemade tortillas made fresh!
data.text: Good Mexican food! Best we've had so far in Bellingham. Great taste but not a place if your looking for something healthy. But if you want healthy don't pick Mexican. :)

data.title: Small restaurant big Mexican food & service
data.text: Try their mole Enchiladas or anything on the menu.  Very personal service with Mexican music playing.  Flan is an 8 of 10.

data.title: Authentic Mexican
data.text: If you're looking for authentic Mexican food this is the place to go. The salsa is worth the trip alone. The service is always friendly and the food is consistently tasty.

data.title: Good Mexican at reasonable price
data.text: Tadeos is my favorite local Mexican restaurant on Holly just north of Railroad Ave. in downtown Bellingham.  Always good food with complimentary 'good' salsa and chips, friendly service and reasonable prices.  They just opened their second location on Northwest Ave across from Yeagers  Sporting Good store with the same menu as their downtown location - it's a large restaurant if you have a bigger group.

data.title: Order a la carte!
data.text: Love this little family-run restaurant. The meats are awesome and the homemade tortillas are delicious. Order a la carte - you can try several things instead of just ordering a combo plate. Although the pollo a la crema is pretty tasty...

data.title: Kinda Mediocre
data.text: Positive stuff first: good service, fresh ingredients, cute atmosphere. But it was a little plain. The tostada was the best but the tacos lacked enough flavour.

data.title: A Good Find
data.text: For years, when we've gone to Bellingham, we've always gone to Mi Mexico near Bellis Fair.  Today we wanted to find something different and so we tried Tadeo's.  The food was very good.  We all loved the fact that the tortilla chips were unsalted.  We also felt the quality of the ingredients was excellent.  Lean, well seasoned meats, fantastic guacamole (the cook told us he made it with cilantro, tomatoes, avocados and olive oil), and really nice service.
